# Thrive Realtime Voice Platform - Project Structure

This is a TypeScript monorepo for a realtime voice platform built with OpenAI's Realtime API.

## Architecture Overview

The platform consists of several interconnected packages:

- **@thrive/realtime-contracts**: Core TypeScript interfaces and types (no dependencies)
- **@thrive/realtime-core**: Core runtime logic for realtime connections
- **@thrive/realtime-observability**: Logging and monitoring utilities
- **@thrive/realtime-config**: Configuration management and feature flags
- **@thrive/realtime-auth-supabase**: Supabase authentication provider
- **@thrive/realtime-ui-components**: React UI components (shadcn/ui based)
- **@thrive/realtime-usage**: Usage tracking and cost estimation
- **@thrive/realtime-security**: Security utilities and rate limiting
- **@thrive/realtime-sre**: Site reliability engineering tools
- **@thrive/realtime-store-prisma**: Database layer with Prisma
- **@thrive/realtime-tool-gateway**: Tool execution with RAG support
- **@thrive/realtime-transport-webrtc**: WebRTC transport implementation
- **@thrive/realtime-transport-websocket**: WebSocket transport implementation

## Key Files

- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Root package configuration with workspaces
- [turbo.json](mdc:turbo.json) - Turborepo build pipeline configuration
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - Root TypeScript configuration
- [pnpm-workspace.yaml](mdc:pnpm-workspace.yaml) - PNPM workspace configuration

## Package Structure

Each package follows this structure:

- `src/` - Source TypeScript files
- `dist/` - Compiled JavaScript output
- `package.json` - Package configuration
- `tsconfig.json` - Package-specific TypeScript config
- `README.md` - Package documentation

## Build System

- Uses Turborepo for monorepo management
- PNPM for package management
- TypeScript for type safety
- All packages build to `dist/` directory
- Dependencies are managed at package level with workspace references
